<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-574-323  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 574 323.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Oct 12 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>SSA puts POMS on CD-ROM. (Social Security Agency, Procedures andOperations Manual System, compact disk-read only memory)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McCormick, John.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Social Security AdministrationCD-ROMGovernment AgencyElectronic Data ProcessingData basesCost Reduction.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>SSA PUTS POMS ON CD-ROM WASHINGTON, D.C., U.S.A., 1990 OCT 12 (NB) -- TheSocial Security Agency (SSA) has placed its 30,000 page Procedures andOperations Manual System or POMS on a single CD-ROM disc in a project thatcost $90,000.andM;The yearly cost of publishing the hard copy version of the POMS is reportedly$2.5 million per year, while SSA spokesperson Reds Horrocks says it will onlycost a half million dollars to maintain the CD-ROM based system.andM;POMS is used at nearly 1,500 SSA field offices.andM;(John McCormick/19901012)</TEXT></DOC>